Wild Shape

Wild Shape lets a druid wear a spirit animal form.  Each
form is learned as its own druid spell, and higher mastery
of that form improves its strength and duration.

Commands:
  wildshape wolf
  wildshape bear
  wildshape hawk
  wildshape serpent
  unshift

Forms:

  Wolf
    Guild level: 6
    Cost: 45 spell points
    Duration: 60 seconds + 30 seconds per wolf mastery level
    Effect: changes your race and visible form to a spirit-wolf
            and grants a dodge bonus.

  Bear
    Guild level: 10
    Cost: 55 spell points
    Duration: 60 seconds + 35 seconds per bear mastery level
    Effect: changes your race and visible form to a spirit-bear
            and grants a constitution bonus.

  Hawk
    Guild level: 12
    Cost: 60 spell points
    Duration: 55 seconds + 32 seconds per hawk mastery level
    Effect: changes your race and visible form to a spirit-hawk
            and grants a dexterity bonus.

  Serpent
    Guild level: 14
    Cost: 68 spell points
    Duration: 55 seconds + 33 seconds per serpent mastery level
    Effect: changes your race and visible form to a spirit-serpent
            and grants a strength bonus.

Terrain:

  Wolf and bear last longer in forest, plains, jungle, swamp,
  hills, farm, and path terrain.

  Hawk lasts longer in sky, mountain, forest, plains, jungle,
  hills, and path terrain.

  Serpent lasts longer in swamp, jungle, forest, underground,
  river, and lake terrain.

  When the terrain is favorable, the duration is increased by
  half.

Restrictions:

  Shifting automatically unequips your worn and wielded gear.
  While shifted, many speaking, study, spell, and guild power
  commands are blocked because the spirit body cannot perform
  them.  Use unshift to return to your natural form early.

  You may only wear one spirit form at a time.  When a form
  ends, the spirit requires a short recovery before you can
  wildshape again.

